comments.body:
@derekwaynecarr Is it OK to run systemd agnostic runtimes on a machine running systemd? I'd hope the answer is yes. Kubelet can create a slice for the pod and then let the runtime use the slice cgroups for managing containers.

Kubelet can accept cgroup paths based on the driver. Not doing that will definitely affect usability. 

When interacting with runtimes, can we have the kubelet use cgroupfs path and let runtimes convert to an appropriate format based on their needs?

